      • getTimestampPredicateCondition

        public String getTimestampPredicateCondition(String column,
                                             long value,
                                             String valueFormat,
                                             String operator)
        Oracle timestamp can go up to 9 digit precision. Existing behavior of Gobblin on extractor is to support up to second and Oracle extractor will keep the same behavior. timestamp predicate condition for types like timestamp
        Returns:
        predicate condition (LastModifiedTimestamp >= 2014-01-01T00:00:00.000Z and LastModifiedTimestamp <= 2014-01-10T15:05:00.000Z)
        See Also:
        ProtocolSpecificLayer.getTimestampPredicateCondition(java.lang.String, long, java.lang.String, java.lang.String)
